Mohammed Munirat Nasir, Gusau Zamfara State deputy governor, Malam Ibrahim, Wakkala Muhammad, has lauded Supreme Court judgement that voided the primaries of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in state. A statement signed by Director-General (Press Affairs) office of the deputy governor, Malam Yusuf, Idris Gusau, said the judgment was a pointer to the impartiality of the judiciary. “This is a victory for democracy; the judgement has restored the confidence of Nigerians in the judiciary sector; and this judgement is a work of truth against falsehood,” he said.